# AB Scheduler registry — the unattended CODE-task loop.
# LIVE copy lives at ~/.gsai/ab-scheduler/projects.conf (machine-global, NOT in
# this repo). Managed by ab-scheduler-ctl.sh {register,unregister}. This file is
# only a template showing the format.
#
# Format:  name|absolute-project-dir|launchd-base-minute
# One line = one repo that gets its own launchd job + backlog/{queue,blocked}.
# CODE projects only — content/brand work stays on the control plane.
#
# The base minute is the first fire each hour; the worker fires again at
# base+15 / base+30 / base+45 (every 15 min) when 4 entries are in the plist,
# or base / base+30 (every 30 min) for 2 entries. Stagger bases across repos so
# they don't all wake at once.
my-app|/Users/you/Code/my-app|0
another-service|/Users/you/Code/another-service|8
